## SECTION B — Java Test Rules

### B1 — Use AssertJ, not JUnit assertions
AssertJ produces better failure messages and has a fluent API.

```java
// BAD
assertEquals(3, results.size());
assertTrue(results.get(0).score() > 0.60);

// GOOD
assertThat(results).hasSize(3);
assertThat(results.get(0).score()).isGreaterThan(0.60);
assertThat(results).extracting(SearchHit::language).containsOnly("bn");
```

### B2 — Unit tests use @ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class IngestServiceTest {

    @Mock QdrantClient qdrantClient;
    @Mock EmbedSidecarClient embedClient;
    @InjectMocks IngestService ingestService;

    @Test
    void should_skip_existing_documents_when_upsert_mode_is_skip_existing() {
        // ...
    }
}
```

### B3 — Integration tests use @SpringBootTest + Testcontainers
```java
@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)
@Testcontainers
@Tag("integration")
class SearchControllerIT {

    @Container
    static GenericContainer<?> qdrant =
        new GenericContainer<>("qdrant/qdrant:latest")
            .withExposedPorts(6333);

    @Autowired TestRestTemplate restTemplate;

    @Test
    void should_return_ranked_results_when_querying_seeded_collection() {
        // seed → search → assert
    }
}
```

### B4 — Controller tests use @WebMvcTest
Do not use `@SpringBootTest` for controller-only tests. `@WebMvcTest` is faster
and more focused.

```java
@WebMvcTest(SearchController.class)
class SearchControllerTest {

    @Autowired MockMvc mvc;
    @MockBean SearchService searchService;

    @Test
    void should_return_400_when_query_is_blank() throws Exception {
        mvc.perform(post("/api/search")
                .contentType(APPLICATION_JSON)
                .content("""{"query":"","collection":"news_radar"}"""))
            .andExpect(status().isBadRequest())
            .andExpect(jsonPath("$.error").exists());
    }
}
```

### B5 — JSON assertions use jsonPath or typed deserialization
Never assert on raw JSON strings. Use `jsonPath` in MockMvc tests or
deserialize to the response DTO for comparison.

```java
// BAD
assertTrue(response.contains("\"ingested\":3"));

// GOOD
assertThat(response.getIngested()).isEqualTo(3);
// or
mvc.perform(...).andExpect(jsonPath("$.ingested").value(3));
```

### B6 — WireMock for external HTTP dependencies in unit tests
`QueryEmbeddingService` and `LLMSynthesisService` call external services.
Use WireMock to simulate them in unit tests — not real services.

```java
@RegisterExtension
static WireMockExtension embedSidecar = WireMockExtension.newInstance()
    .options(wireMockConfig().dynamicPort())
    .build();

@BeforeEach
void setUp() {
    embedSidecar.stubFor(post(urlEqualTo("/api/embed"))
        .willReturn(okJson("""{"vector":[0.1,0.2],"dimensions":2}""")));
}
```

### B7 — Verify latency_ms is populated correctly
Every search and ingest integration test must assert that `latency_ms`
fields are present and non-zero.

```java
assertThat(response.latencyMs().embed()).isPositive();
assertThat(response.latencyMs().search()).isPositive();
assertThat(response.latencyMs().total()).isGreaterThan(
    response.latencyMs().embed() + response.latencyMs().search()
);
```

### B8 — Test both search modes explicitly
Every search integration test runs both `mode=search` and `mode=rag`
against the same query. The two responses must differ in predictable ways.

```java
@Test void should_return_null_summary_in_search_mode() { ... }
@Test void should_return_non_empty_summary_in_rag_mode() { ... }
```

### B9 — Parameterized tests for filter combinations
Use `@ParameterizedTest` for filter testing — do not write one test per filter.

```java
@ParameterizedTest
@MethodSource("filterCombinations")
void should_filter_results_correctly(SearchFilters filters, int expectedCount) {
    SearchResponse response = searchService.search("floods in Dhaka", "news_radar",
        10, 0.60, "search", filters);
    assertThat(response.results()).hasSize(expectedCount);
}

static Stream<Arguments> filterCombinations() {
    return Stream.of(
        arguments(new SearchFilters("bn", null, null, null), 4),  // 4 Bangla articles
        arguments(new SearchFilters("en", null, null, null), 4),  // 4 English articles
        arguments(new SearchFilters(null, "2026-06-15", "2026-06-15", null), 2)
    );
}
```

