## SECTION D — TypeScript / React Test Rules

### D1 — React Testing Library, not Enzyme
Never use Enzyme. All component tests use `@testing-library/react`.
Query priority: `getByRole` > `getByLabelText` > `getByText` > `getByTestId`.

```typescript
// BAD
wrapper.find('.qv-mode-btn').at(1).simulate('click');

// GOOD
await userEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /RAG/i }));
```

### D2 — MSW for all API mocking
All API calls in component and hook tests are intercepted by MSW handlers.
No `jest.mock('fetch')` or manual fetch mocking.

```typescript
// src/__tests__/handlers.ts
export const handlers = [
  http.post('/api/search', () =>
    HttpResponse.json(mockSearchResponse)
  ),
  http.get('/api/health', () =>
    HttpResponse.json({ status: 'ok', qdrant: 'connected',
                        ollama: 'connected', embed_sidecar: 'connected' })
  ),
];
```

### D3 — Test user interactions, not implementation
```typescript
// BAD — tests internal state
expect(component.state.mode).toBe('rag');

// GOOD — tests what the user sees
await userEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /RAG/i }));
expect(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /RAG/i })).toHaveClass('on');
```

### D4 — Every component tests loading and error states
```typescript
it('should show skeleton while search is loading', async () => {
  server.use(http.post('/api/search', () => new Promise(() => {}))); // never resolves
  render(<App />);
  await userEvent.type(screen.getByRole('searchbox'), 'floods in Dhaka{Enter}');
  expect(screen.getByTestId('search-skeleton')).toBeInTheDocument();
});

it('should show error banner when API returns 500', async () => {
  server.use(http.post('/api/search', () => HttpResponse.error()));
  render(<App />);
  await userEvent.type(screen.getByRole('searchbox'), 'floods in Dhaka{Enter}');
  expect(screen.getByRole('alert')).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

### D5 — useSearch hook tested in isolation via renderHook
```typescript
it('should update results when search completes', async () => {
  const { result } = renderHook(() => useSearch());

  act(() => { result.current.search({ query: 'floods', collection: 'news_radar' }); });

  await waitFor(() => expect(result.current.loading).toBe(false));
  expect(result.current.results).toHaveLength(4);
  expect(result.current.error).toBeNull();
});
```

### D6 — Accessibility tested with axe-core
Every page-level component (`App`, `SearchWidget`) must pass axe-core
accessibility audit in tests.

```typescript
import { axe, toHaveNoViolations } from 'jest-axe';
expect.extend(toHaveNoViolations);

it('should have no accessibility violations', async () => {
  const { container } = render(<App />);
  const results = await axe(container);
  expect(results).toHaveNoViolations();
});
```

### D7 — SearchWidget props contract tested
The MFE widget must have tests for every prop in `SearchWidgetProps`:
- default values when optional props are omitted
- `onResultClick` fires with the correct `SearchResult` argument
- `theme` prop changes CSS class / data attribute
- `filters` prop pre-populates filter chips

