## SECTION E — Integration + E2E Test Rules

### E1 — Integration tests use a shared fixture corpus
All integration tests that seed Qdrant use `fixtures/news_radar_dhaka_floods.json`.
Never create ad-hoc fixture data in integration test code.

```java
// GOOD
@BeforeAll
static void seedQdrant() throws Exception {
    String fixture = Files.readString(Path.of("fixtures/news_radar_dhaka_floods.json"));
    // seed via ingest API
}
```

### E2 — Integration tests assert the full response shape
Do not assert only a single field. Assert the entire response structure
against the SPEC §6 contract.

```java
@Test
void should_return_complete_search_response_shape() {
    SearchResponse r = restTemplate.postForObject("/api/search", request, SearchResponse.class);

    assertThat(r.query()).isEqualTo("floods in Dhaka last week");
    assertThat(r.mode()).isEqualTo("search");
    assertThat(r.summary()).isNull();                             // search mode
    assertThat(r.results()).isNotEmpty();
    assertThat(r.latencyMs().embed()).isPositive();
    assertThat(r.latencyMs().search()).isPositive();
    assertThat(r.latencyMs().total()).isPositive();
    assertThat(r.latencyMs().synthesis()).isNull();               // search mode
}
```

### E3 — E2E tests cover the full user journey
Playwright E2E tests must cover exactly the scenarios in the mock UI:

1. Open UI → verify health status pills show connected
2. Type "floods in Dhaka last week" → press Enter
3. Verify ≥ 4 result cards appear
4. Verify top result score > 0.60
5. Toggle to RAG mode → verify AI summary panel appears
6. Verify latency breakdown is shown
7. Click a result card → verify URL opens

### E4 — E2E tests are deterministic
E2E tests run against a pre-seeded Qdrant instance (via `make seed`).
The seed script is idempotent. E2E tests never seed inside the test itself.

### E5 — Performance baselines are asserted in integration tests
```java
@Test
void search_mode_completes_within_500ms() {
    long start = System.currentTimeMillis();
    SearchResponse r = searchService.search(query, collection, 10, 0.60, "search", null);
    long elapsed = System.currentTimeMillis() - start;

    assertThat(elapsed).isLessThan(500L);
    assertThat(r.latencyMs().total()).isLessThan(500L);
}
```

Baselines from SPEC §15:
- Search mode: < 500ms
- RAG mode: < 10s (conservative — Ollama on CPU)

### E6 — Smoke test is a standalone script
`scripts/e2e-smoke.sh` must be runnable without Playwright installed.
It uses only `curl` to verify the critical path:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e

echo "=== Queriva smoke test ==="

echo "1. Health check..."
curl -sf http://localhost:8080/api/health | grep '"status":"ok"'

echo "2. Create collection..."
curl -sf -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/ingest/collection \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"collection":"smoke_test","vector_size":768,"distance":"Cosine"}'

echo "3. Ingest one document..."
curl -sf -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/ingest/documents \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"collection":"smoke_test","documents":[{"id":"s1","title":"Smoke test","body":"This is a smoke test document for Queriva.","source":"test","language":"en"}]}'

echo "4. Search..."
RESULT=$(curl -sf -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/search \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"query":"smoke test","collection":"smoke_test","top_k":1,"mode":"search"}')
echo "$RESULT" | grep '"results"'

echo "5. Cleanup..."
curl -sf -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/ingest/collection/smoke_test

echo "=== Smoke test PASSED ==="
```
